snippet.textDisplay: maybe cause it was easy to find this game in 90s, easy to play and 2 player mode that you can help your friend to finish the game (different other good racing games that you just have versus mode with no CPU). Brazil early 90s suffered with insane inflation, so, everything was hard to buy, it was very difficult to get a videogame, and when you had it, rarely you could buy new games, that's why everyone rent it or went to friend's house to play together with them... that's why every huge success game in Brazil, was games that had 2 player coop-mode, that take days and days to beat the game (the reason that you love when your friends come to your house to help you) or has a very very very good replay at versus mode (like Street Fighter II and Mortal Kombat II). Single player games wasn't so popular...
